title: Haricot Table, ca. 1810
medium: mahogany veneer on pine; black leather top; brass gallery
creditline: Bequest of Mrs. John Innes Kane
description: Kidney shaped table with pierced brass gallery about top, back and sides. Turned, tapering legs splay out slightly toward base, united by turned baluster stretchers in X-shape, square in section at point of crossing. Leather panel in top has tooled decoration about edge.

tombstone.epitaph: Haricot Table, ca. 1810. mahogany veneer on pine; black leather top; brass gallery. Bequest of Mrs. John Innes Kane. 1926-22-364.
